-- Legal & General May Name Wilson as Chief Executive, Sky Reports
-- B y   N e i l   C a l l a n a n
-- 2012-05-05T16:15:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-05/legal-general-may-name-wilson-as-chief-executive-sky-reports.html
Legal & General Group Plc. (LGEN) , an
insurance and pension provider that is the biggest investor in
the U.K. stock market, may name current finance director Nigel Wilson as its new chief executive officer next week, Sky said,
citing people close to the matter.  Wilson, whose appointment is subject to the approval of the
Financial Services Authority, would succeed Tim Breedon who will
step down later this year, Sky reported. L&G declined to
comment, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Neil Callanan in London at 
 ncallanan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Andrew Blackman  at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 